                  , Nephew, as 'tis said, to my Lord Gerard
            </rs>; the circumstances of which, were these: The Party killed, with several other young Gentlemen, being late abroad, on the tenth of this instant in Holborn, took it in their way to come through Whetstones park, where spying Lights in Peetly's house, they knocked hard at the door, and bid him open it, the which he refusing, one or more of them, began to break the windows, and having Linkmen with them, they threw up lighted Links, the which, as Peetly said, did set fire to some Linnen in a Closet, at which he being Allarumed, got his Carbine in his hand, charged with small Bullets, and pursued them up <placeName id="t16810117-6-crimeloc25">great Queen-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16810117-6-crimeloc25" type="placeName" value="great Queen-street"></interp>
